From: OpenWrt Team <openwrt-devel@lists.openwrt.org>
Subject: Fix ipip6 MTU 9000 support

Linux kernel ipip6 tunnel devices have a low default max_mtu limit,
which prevents setting MTU to 9000 for jumbo frames support. This
causes issues with HomeProxy Tun TCP/UDP proxy for IPv6 traffic.

Set dev->max_mtu to 9000 in ip6_tnl_newlink to allow MTU 9000
configuration on ipip6 tunnel devices.

Signed-off-by: OpenWrt Team <openwrt-devel@lists.openwrt.org>
---
 net/ipv6/ip6_tunnel.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/net/ipv6/ip6_tunnel.c
+++ b/net/ipv6/ip6_tunnel.c
@@ -2130,6 +2130,7 @@ static int ip6_tnl_newlink(struct net_de
 {
 	struct ip6_tnl *t = netdev_priv(dev);
 	struct ip6_tnl_parm p;
+	dev->max_mtu = 9000;

 	ip6_tnl_parm_from_user(&p, t);
 	p.link = IFLA_IPTUN_LINK;
